caption: High end Mexican place within Division Street. Quality and presentation is great, great ingredients and amazing drinks.

Went here for the first time when Big Star had waaay too long a line. Takito Kitchen had no line and some damn good tacos. Came back recently during COVID, plenty of outdoor space, reservations were easy. Food as good as always.  The tacos are usually a bit unique which I love. Last time I had a lamb taco, kinda Mediterranean flavor, delicious. But I'll never forget I had a pork belly taco the first time I went and it was just this huge, rich, flavor-packed slab of meat. Crisp but melt in your mouth delicious.  They're not the cheapest tacos, but well worth it.
Love! Brunch is amazing and very good pricing. Bottomless mimosas were $12! And they are not stingy. They make sure you're craft is full at all times.
I loved the experience and food!! The Chicken Tinga was sensational and perfect! The Strawberry Margarita was to die for!!🍹🥰
Excellent spot for midday brunch on a Sunday. The bottomless mimosa option is a must
Love Takito Kitchen! Great food and service. Always a pleasant experience. We have had Anna a few times as our server, so great! Will continue to come here

Wow, such a cool and inviting space! Everything was wonderful (service, food, COVID guidelines, drinks, etc.).  Tacos- on point and delicious  Drinks- very good and worth it! I got the small (which at some places it’s a large). The large- size of a fish bowl!  Service- amazing, so tentative and kind (we had Ana M.)  Food in general- so, so good.  I will be back, and recommend to anyone!
Great chorizo omelette and mezcal mule. The ambience seemed authentic and the crowd of patrons had a good vibe. Glad me and my fiancé randomly stopped in

I recently went to go eat here. First time at this place and let me tell you the food was good but the drinks bomb!! I ordered a couple of margaritas and they did not disappoint! I will be returning soon! And the serve I received was marvelous! Ana was so attentive, friendly!

This is our favorite taco place! The entire menu is gluten free which is amazing for me! The staff is excellent, service is always phenomenal and the margaritas are so so good! Carlos always takes excellent care of us. Can't wait to go back!

I've been here several times, and have always had so much fun! The food is delicious and the drinks are strong. Lol It's a great deal, especially compared to the neighborhood. The staff is friendly and inviting, but I have to single out Vince! He's been my server a couple of times, and has always been very helpful, kind, and thorough. He makes sure my friends and I are perfectly taken care of! I can't recommend this place enough.

I had a terrible experience here. We ordered 2 margaritas which ended up being $45 and they weren’t even good. After getting our drinks our waiter never came back so we eventually had to flag him over to get the check because we decided we didn’t even want to bother with ordering food. We went across the street to another restaurant and had great food and drinks. I will never go back to Takito Kitchen.

This restaurant is not following the Chicago covid restrictions. I specifically made a reservation for an outdoor dining experience. When we arrived there was a curtain up hiding about 20+ indoor diners, no open windows, no masks in sight, all sitting closer than 6’. The host led us to an indoor table without even checking our reservation. We ended up leaving and couldn’t find another dinner spot, a complete waste of a night because of this restaurants online shadiness !
Wonderful food, great service...we will be going back! A LOT

Cookie cutter mediocre Mexican fare delivered with a helping portion of pretentiousness. Food was just okay, drink selection abysmal. How does a Mexican joint in Chicago have such a poor tequila and mezcal selection? Overall, a totally forgettable experience I wouldn't recommend, especially to discerning Mexican food and tequila/mezcal aficionados.
Carlos was the best! He made my bday extra special and we never had empty glasses. 10/10!

Brunch was amazing. The bottomless mimosas were surprisingly tasty 😳 it wasn't the cheap stuff most restaurants use (or at least it didn't taste like it 😅). The only issue we had was taken care immediately, great customer service.
The shrimp tacos are good and the margaritas are excellent!
Courteous staff, delicious food, and incredibly good avocado guacamole. I'm around the area and will definitely be making a return for the chicken tacos!!
Was ok. Food (tacos) was a bit bland. No real spice, spices, or flavor. Solidly filling amount of food though.
Excellent service and even better happy hour ($6 small margs, those giant doubles are $12)! Love this place
Tequila time!🤫
I've been here 3 times and have always had a good experience. The space is small, but the margaritas are delicious and the tacos are consistently good!

I love this place so much! No matter what I always come here every time I’m in Chicago. The best tacos I ever had and great selection of delicious margaritas. Friendly stuff and fast service. Can’t wait to come back!
Those tacos are amazing. Pork belly tacos - must have! (If you not vegetarian) Can not wait until this place reopen. :-)

Lived up to the name.  The gourmet tacos were all deliciousness.. my favorites were the barbacoa and pork belly, if we hadn't ordered so many I would have got more of these.  The only slight disappointment was the shrimp ceviche "shareable" plate.. - not nearly enough to share , being on the enough for 2 side of a menu I expected way more ceviche on the giant bed of greens - on the plus side, it was good and the giant chips were yummy ( and there were 3 times as many chips as needed for mediocre serving of ceviche ).  Nice Latino themed beverage selection.  Think I'll be back, hope they fix the shrimp ceviche situation by then 😉
Fish tacos were ok (not great), and the Chips salsa were salty.. was disappointed with the visit
Delicious food. Bottomless mimosas. Fun place to have a birthday.
One of my favorite brunch places, great for dinner too. A+ atmosphere and very friendly staff with quick service. Highly recommend.

Always attentive staff, great service, nice environment,  good food, and the manager is amazing. My little lady also works here and I love stopping by after work to visit here because I love her smile
Tasty yumy super over priced margaritas. Delicious yummy overpriced tacos. Hard to find parking. Pushy service. Yin yen review. Although I like the drinks and the food everything is way over priced.

Best taco joint/pub in Chicago!!! Great selection of flavorful tacos and salsa. Always very fresh. They even make their own tortillas and chips as well as hot sauce😋😋😋😋. Their menu changes a bit every few months. I love love love their beef barbacoa as well as the lamb sausage tacos. Their fish tacos  incrusted with coconut won’t disappoint you. Very Friendly staff. Jamie and Carlos are our favorite general managers Jaime is awesome and super attentive. Highly recommend this restaurant. Can’t wait to go back. Go get some tacos now !

Recently checked out Takito Kitchen (I work near by and have always had my eye on it) and I instantly fell in love! The vibe and energy from the staff is great. It’s a nice environment to enjoy the great food they offer. I am vegan and ordered the vegan mushrooms tacos! They had so much flavor! My omnivore husband loved them too! They also have a great drink menu! We will absolutely be back. I’ll definitely be recommending this place to my friends & family. You won’t regret trying this place out!

Their whole menu is gluten free! And everything was so good. We tried the chips and seasonal salsa, steak tacos, and avocado rice, and everything was delicious. Service was good too. Overall great experience!

We went here to kick off a bachelorette party, and it was amazing!! Bottomless mimosas served in pitchers that kept coming. Our waiter was so kind and fast with service. Plus the food? Soo good! I ordered the breakfast tacos with coffee braised beef which was a great serving and so tasty. Highly recommend for a lit brunch!!
Gourmet flavors at reasonable prices.
Amazing

Tacos were pretty good. Queso wasn’t really queso. It was more like flaming cheese, which was good, but obviously not what I’m expecting when I order queso. The tacos were tasty but you have to order 2 of the same kind no matter how many Youre getting. It’s fine, but would’ve liked to have had 2 different ones instead of 2 of the same, especially for the price.
Tacos and appetizers we're outstanding.  Strong drink menu, though no wine?  Crazy. Good service.  We will be back.
Quali-T! Best brunch in the neighborhood. Seriously. You can’t beat their bottomless deals. Not to mention the food, too. Find me here every weekend.
the while menu is gluten free and amazing. I love their margaritas.
We loved the vibe here! Amazing tacos, pine nuts an avocado puree is as well, great service! Would love a Takito in Orlando downtown!

Great spot for bottomless mimosas - heavy pour and the wait staff keeps them coming! The food portions are huge but the quality has been great - highly recommend the pork belly sope. The cowboy coffee is also worth a try!
Best bottomless brunch in town.
Went for some drinks. The drinks were delicious and the service was great. I'll be returning for a meal sometime soon.

A friend and I decided to try something new this weekend before exploring the craft festival. We were pleasantly surprised to discover they offer bottomless mimosas on Saturday, we just didn't get there early enough to try them. The small is small, and they were packed, but we sat there for about 10 minutes with servers serving the two tables on either side of us and ignoring us. We finally asked one server of she was our server and she said no and walked off. Didn't offer to find out who our server was, get is started with drinks, or anything. I finally walked up to someone else and explained that we had been sitting a while and still didn't even have water. She apologized and immediately took our order and even gave is half off our margaritas, which was nice. The cucumber margarita had a nice flavor and a good strong kick.  The food came out fairly quickly once we did order but I was disappointed in the lack of flavor. I ordered the Amish chicken omelette and I ended up drowning it in salsa because of the bland flavor. My friend ordered 3 different tacos and only liked one of them. Neither one of us are picky eaters, their food just wasn't for us apparently. I honestly probably won't be going back.
Great tacos and margs!

Fantastic!! Had the lamb and shrimp tacos. Probably one of the best I've had in Chicago so far. Delicious modern flavors. Love it! But the highlight was the Queso Fundido. And then, the Coffee Flan!! Don't miss both of these unassuming menu items. Blast of flavor

We stopped in on Sunday afternoon. There weren't many other people there and the service was great. We had the pistachio tomatillo salsa, fantastic. We decided to also have the fish tacos. There is a coconut sauce that is unexpected and perfect. We had eaten here previously and the quality is just as good as the last time about a year ago.
Very friendly staff. Adam was very excellent in service and is great to converse with

Just had a couple cucumber margaritas and a quick appetizer and omfg this place is amazing.  The drinks came out fast and they were perfect. The app was out quickly even though they were very busy and it was amazing.  Our server was there and attentive but not there so much to where it was annoying.  I work in a restaurant and this place offers exactly the sort of service we strive to give our guests! Perfect!!!  A+++
Tasty tacos!
Awesome atmosphere, great service and staff. Went during bottomless mimosas and had the best time!!!
Tacos: 🔥🔥 Margaritas: Literally 🔥
Food is good
Great brunch! Delicious Mexican Twists!

This place has killer coffee braised beef barbacoa tacos. I dream about them. Their Margaritas are really tasty and they have an awesome cheesy polenta with bacon crumbles on top. I highly recommend this place if you're into modern Mexican.

Good food, expensive for what it is, and horrible service. Took my boyfriend and friends out last weekend, utterly embarrassed by the service considering we paid almost $300 for dinner. I have been a loyal customer for over 3 years but I'm sad to say I will no longer be returning.

The food and atmosphere were very unique. Definitely not a common dinner place, but is a great special occasion spot. The ceviche was delicious and everyone enjoyed their tacos. With a party of seven we spent an easy hundred dollars.
I had some delicious vegan tacos here today.  Highly recommend!
Wonderful St. Paddy's Brunch
My favorite Mexican spot in Wicker Park. Gluten free tacos are delicious but I especially love the margaritas.
Yummy margaritas.
Great food and atmosphere. Prices are good and food is really good. Great margaritas.
Slow service and underwhelming food. Much better taco options in the area.

Not the best place for someone looking for vegetarian tacos, but the food was good and the vibe is live. We liked the atmosphere, except the music is almost too loud to be able to converse with your fellow diners. We would recommend the salad and the mushroom tacos, if you’re looking for vegetarian options.
Great selection of margaritas. The shared plates are to due for
Delicious food and even better service
Good food and prices. Long wait times.
Very good tasty  and good service
Yummy, and quick!
Great flavors. Fresh ingredients. Great plate presentations. Great service. Cool vibe. Elevated Street Mexican without pretentiousness.

Lazy and poor customer service! Went in at 9:30pm, and the hostess said sorry we’re closed. Mind you online and the writing print on the door said they close at 10pm! Will never return due to lack of customer service and just plain out liars, inconsiderate humans work here, believe me. P.S. note - all the other reviews says slow customer service and have horrible attitude problems believe that, it’s because them people don’t care about ANYONE who walk through that door, them employees just want their Check that’s it that’s all. You can tell they hate their job.     Do yourself a favor and don’t go here, it’s way better food around in this area, and trust me the tacos isn’t merely better than Taco Bell.

Delicious margaritas!! We had the Takito and tamarindo cilantro margaritas. The only issue is that on Friday-Sunday they have strict rules regarding the minimum tacos that you can order. You must purchase at least 2 of the same taco. This prevented me from trying a variety of tacos, instead of trying 3 of their tacos (I wanted 1 of their fried fish, 1 shrimp and 1 barbacoa) I was restricted to only 1 since I had to order minimum of 2 tacos of the same kind?? This may work for groups but when your companion is vegan this does not work. The coconut flan was also well done.
It was decent.  Here from out of town.  Enjoying lots of appetizers with family that lives in Chicago. Gluten free meals and nice drinks
Always a great place for brunch!
Gluten free

Ate here for brunch this morning. We went with a big group after the Chicago Marathon. We had a reservation, but the wait staff was not prepared for our group (service was slow). Outside of that, the food and ambience were great! Overall a good experience and would go back!

Wanted to run out for a late night snack seeing that they close at 10p, we arrived at 9:27p and was denied service. I had paid for parking, mind you.   Hostess Mora told us that they were closed, and I said you close at 10p and she replied ooohhh yea no it's 9:27 yea we're closed then she called out to who seemed to be the manager which also looked at the time and said yea we're closed. I guess you have to come at a certain time to get service here, what maybe 6  7, 8, 9, what 9:15 -20? IDK ,But they won't have to worry about us at anytime anymore. UNPROFESSIONAL  , POOR CUSTOMER SERVICE,  BECAUSE THEY DON'T WANT TO WORK UNTIL CLOSING

I've got to be honest, I was disappointed in this place. I had heard that it was good, so I went in with high hopes. We ordered one of the salsas. I was surprised that they would actually charge you for salsa and chips, and even moreso when it arrived. It was just a runny couple tablespoons of salsa with about 12 large chips. They charge 0.50 for more chips. Then, we ordered tacos. The tacos are a minimum of 2 per order, so my fiancee and I ordered 3 different kinds to try a couple. I asked the waiter if they could put the 3 different tacos on 2 plates. He said that they couldn't do that. We got the fish, lamb merguez, and the barbacoa. The fish was good. The hibiscus tortilla made them look cool. The lamb was a sausage, which was a little unusual in a taco, but not bad. The barbacoa was stringy. Overall, I think this place is overpriced. I can't say that I'll be coming back.
Delicious tacos and avocado rice..yummy.

We just moved to the area so I've been asking for recommendations and this place has come up several times.  Stopped in for a bite and drink and absolutely loved it.  Everything from food, drink selection and decor was perfect.
Decent food. Horrible service, bad drinks.

Not your typical taqueria. It's upscale and chef inspired. The place is clean, the staff is attentive and the food is delicious. My favorites were the pork belly taco, the queso fundido and the guacamole.
Mario is the man
Good food, and amazing brunch deals!

Really nice space, and the service was great, but I really wasn't a fan of the food.  Instead of chips and salsa, you get something that is more like crackers, and some weird dipping sauces.  The tacos were just a little too "inventive" for my taste.  Also, this location doesn't have a bar to sit at.  I'm a bar guy.  I like sitting at the bar, and if a place that serves drinks doesn't have a bar I can sit at, it weirds me out a little.
Best margaritas and tacos
Upscale Mexican fusion. Margaritas, tacos 👌🏻

We def will be back. However the hostess (tonight) need to let customers sit where they're  comfortable and not push people to sit where "she" would sit. The food is gluten free which is a bonus. Ingredients is fresh down to the lime wedges. We had fried chicken tacos, pork belly tacos and fish tacos.  They were all delicious.  Joey was a fantastic server.  Variety of music in the back ground, which was enjoyable. They have a great weekday specials. Be back to try their margaritas and other food items. Need to mention that the owner was personable, introduced himself and ask which taco I enjoy the most.

Such an amazing Wicker Park spot! Nice and friendly staff, that will provide great recommendations for your dining options. Brunch is amazing, highly recommend the Sope. Pro-tip: $10 bottomless mimosas on be weekends until 2:30pm. You can’t got wrong with any of the entrees, because they are all decent portions and absolutely delicious!
Best tacos & margaritas in the city

I have now been to Takito Kitchen 5 times in the last 6 weeks. The tacos are amazing and the margaritas are delicious! Don't skimp out on the trio of salsas... they're are unique and great to add to your tacos.
Fantastic. Fair prices. Original. Delicious.
The smallest tacos ever!!!!
Delicious food! Has the chicken chilaquiles from their brunch menu, really flavorful! Their agua frescas are very refreshing. Service is incredible. Great place!

My first time EVER leaving a restaurant a 1 star. We were visiting Chicago from out of town. We've never been to the restaurant so we figured we would give it a chance. When we walked in we were greeted with a friendly man up front. Then we sat out table, sat at our table some more, annndddd continued to sit at our table. So I glance around to see two servers just chatting away and laughing leaned up against the counter. So we still didn't say anything. After 10 min of just sitting there with not a single wait staff to even get our drink order we left. When stopped why we were leaving we didn't get a "oh I'm so sorry let's get you taken care of right away!" Because that's how we would have handled it being we have both worked in the food industry, we got a "oh ....sorry" like seriously! Never again!
Great drinks!

Great place and vibes here from the fun staff. A fantastic brunch spot with friends, good music and delicious food. The breakfast tacos with coffee braised beef barbacoa is a must! Get a bunch of shared plates and enjoy the fun atmosphere.
Flavored Margaritas are the best! The tacos are unique and the service is great!
Brunch was great. Very nice service. Will definitely go back.
Margaritas were good, tacos just as good. Favorite was fried chicken on Wednesdays and the pork belly.
Good food and drinks
The salsa and tacos were very good. Prices are reasonable.
Love the cocktails!

Loved it!! First timer and googled searched best fish tacos in Chicago and came across this location! Highly highly recommend the fish tacos! And the guacamole puree! Service was great -- overall food was great!
Great food and unlimited mimosas before 2pm. I absolutely adored Margarita and the waitress I called Daria; you'll know who and why.
Delicious food! Get the chilaquiles

Food was amazing, but it took about 15mins to Finally get a waitress but felt rushed while trying to order staff could be friendlier. Also my water cup had lipstick.. My husband's water cup had a hair in it..  We asked for hot sauce it came in a cool little tube inside a cup.. Cup was disgusting had hair and dust so didn't use the hot sauce since the tip was covered in hair and dust .. But food was good.
Good tacos, slightly more than you'd like to pay for tacos but really good flavor. The margaritas were just okay which was disappointing.
Delicious tacos and a variety of tasty margaritas! I will be back. Favs: pineapple marg, ceviche and the coffee beef taco. Yum!
Delicious food and a truly spicy margarita, Takito gets it right. Youthful vibe, cheery atmosphere.

This place was such a surprise the first time I went in. It looks a little underwhelming from outside. But it's much larger than expected inside with an awesome sky light in the back. I love the decor. Not to mention the staff have always been so nice and helpful. Great service, food and drink. A favorite spot of mine in the neighborhood.
Super friendly staff, awesome food, and even better drinks.

I don't know why my original review was taken down, but here it is: Brought my wife and baby daughter there. We sat ourselves down in between three other tables nearby already served and were finishing up. Brought us water...and that was it. I understand the waitress being focused on patrons who are about to pay their checks, but we are your next customers! I tried to make eye contact to get the waitress to come over. I wasn't about to shout across the room to get service. After 20 minutes, we left. And I got the impression the staff working there didn't care.
Great experience. Get the pork belly...

So delicious, absolutely recommend. Good prices, tasty meals, good brunch menu. Pain point: entire menu is gluten-free, but on Sundays they serve a fried item that's flour-based, so anything else that is fried that day is cross-contaminated. Was pretty disappointed that half of their otherwise gluten-free menu was suddenly not an option.

I love this place. Tortillas made fresh to order  topped with fresh ingredients. Lamb merguez is my favorite. Tequilla Thursday, 6 dollar margaritas. I like the spicy one, pineapple serrano, but all sorts of varieties. Friendly, helpful staff.
Awesome tacos and tasty margaritas!!!
Great food, great service. Highly recommend the pork belly tacos.

I'd been at the Lake Street location before and was very excited to try this one out. It's less tasty, very salty tortilla chips and the ceviche was a little disappointing. The cocktails were a little weak. Very different from my experience at the other location.
Great pork belly and fried chicken tacos!
Amazing tacos. The lamb is super delicious!
AMAZING tacos. Flavor city. Enough said.

I really like this place. Its menu is gluten free, pretty much the only place I know  in the city where I can eat fried chicken and fried fish without having to do or myself. Their tacos are trendy and tasty as are their margaritas. Big fan of their taco Tuesday and fried chicken taco Wednesday.  Also, their wait staff goes above and beyond. They put on Obama's farewell speech at my friends and my request, they're very attentive, and they even make me feel good when I make a mistake.  I'm a neighborhood regular.
Loved the tamarindo margarita

The food here is UNBELIEVABLE. The price is.....well, it can sneak up on you, because things aren't that cheap, so you order a couple of things here, and a couple of things there, and suddenly you've spent sixty bucks fer two people! O.O I suppose if you pay attention, though, you can eat well for a pretty low price. Either way, the food is worth it, and the service is AMAZING. A must try for someone wanting Mexican food outside the box. :-)
Much better than its sister store Takito bar. Margs are great and very cool spot.
Wonderful brunch deals! $10 bottomless mimosas and all the meals are cheap. The waiter was very attentive and it wasn't too crowded. I will definitely be going back soon.
Amazing tacos
Inventive mexi food with great libations to go with.

This is a wonderful neighborhood spot. Food literally melts in your mouth the service is the best I've seen anywhere in Chicago. A great selection of drinks and they're made right across from you with an open bar area. The shuffle come out when it's not busy and check on the guest the owner does the same thing. If you're in the area I highly recommend stopping in I'm confident you'll come back

Fabulous! Great food, awesome cocktails.We drove from Plainfield after seeing them on Chicago's best the night before. Totally worth the ride. Marlin was our server and he was wonderful. Mario, the owner came over and spoke to us to thank for coming. Can't wait to go back. See you soon Marlin.
Love the fish tacos!
Prices extremely high and there is no parking
good tacos, would be better with a more defined vegetarian section. For the Indian spice lovers :)
Service was incredibly! Server was so knowledgeable, friendly, and helpful. The margaritas are delicious, and the food is great! Will be back again.

My husband and I hired Takito Kitchen to cater our casual wedding reception. They were fantastic and we cannot recommend them highly enough. The food was delicious and a huge hit with all our guests. First of all, these are some of the tastiest tacos and sides in Chicago. Second of all, the food is prepared in a gluten-free kitchen. This was a huge consideration for us because one of our best friends has celiac disease and has to be very careful with cross contamination. Many places use gluten free ingredients but do not follow the cross contamination processes necessary to make the food safe for people with celiac. Richard Vallejo was very responsive to our questions and worked to create a great menu for us. There were a few minor hiccups with the delivery but Richard went above and beyond to make it right for us in the end. I would hire them again in a heartbeat.

This is my favorite place in Chicago for fancy tacos and margaritas. The menu changes throughout the season and you should always try the seasonal margaritas. My favorite dish is barbacoa, but I love every dish here. It can be really busy, or it can be really empty. Regardless, get some reservations.
Our group had reservations and the group ahead of us was late leaving so we were 10 minutes late getting our table and the manager took care of our first round of margaritas!!  Excellent service!!
Fantastic food, great drinks and staff.
Great fish tacos.
Our server was awesome and so was the atmosphere. The pork belly tacos are currently my favorite as well as the margs! Would definitely recommend this place to friends.
The outside makes it look like a food truck but the inside is awesome! great drinks, solid tacos, and good service.
Good unique food
Very friendly staff and management. Food was phenomenal!! Ashley and Mario came up to our table took time to talk to us and give us a little history of the place. We are definitely coming back.
Cool atmosphere, good service, whole menu is gluten free!
Really calm and fun place.
Food was great, service was amazing. Accommodated us at the drop of a hat. Definitely coming back here the next time I'm in Chicago.
The food was pretty decent and the brunch special had bottomless mimosas and bloody Marys.

Loved loved the steak and fish tacos, salsas were all delicious and avocado pine nut puree was such a unique and interesting blend of flavors. This is definitely a new favorite and when I want tacos in the city am coming here.
Great food (this place actually has elevated tacos unlike some of their competitors) and drinks are fantastic.    Definitely recommend!
The eight-year about a month ago and I think I'll be going there today again. Their Margaritas are awesome and the tacos are on point
Outstanding fresh and flavorful cuisine. The various margaritas were delicious and inventive. The tacos were  uniquely prepared, fresh and tasty. Recommended!
Best Mexican food I've had in Chicago.  Get the blueberry tequila too.

Tacos were delicious but a little expensive and they took awhile to make. I was with a large group so that may have slowed things down but they also gave some people's meals on the same plates and it got confusing at times.
Loved the colorful homemade tortillas! Pork belly and coffee braised beef are a must.
The tacos here are really good, namely the fish, beef and lamb ones.  What I really come here for however, is their margaritas.  The cucumber margarita haunts my dreams.
great tacos, pretty uncommon modern type, but very tasty.

The BEST tacos I have had in Chicago.  These tacos are absolute standouts from tradition, in the best way possible.  The fish taco is not your breaded, fried number.  It is well cooked with a crust and then put with a combination of a mildly spicy jalapeno slaw and a cooling coconut sauce.  The vibrant hibiscus tortilla alone is stunning and then the flavor comes in and it is a must try experience.  The barbacoa is perfectly soft and delicious.  It was succulent without being greasy and was paired with the perfect toppings that held up to the strong braised meat taste.  Takito has a homemade tortilla for each taco to enhance the flavor.  The sauce they added to each matched the meat and the experience as a whole.  I am not just coming back, but I am coming back soon and with friends.
The warmest, welcoming service and jarringly delicious food every time!
Staff was extremely nice. Really good tacos. Dessert was amazing.
Good service and margarita. Guac and tacos werent worth high price tag.
Good food and margaritas. Nice service.
Expensive for tiny tacos, but they tasted good. Staff could be more inviting and friendly.

The best local place for modern tacos and drinks.  The staff is down right some of the best and friendliest staff I've ever met.  The fish tacos are hands down amazing.  The sides are always good... Almost too good!  By far the best margaritas I've ever had.  Get a Big One and enjoy ;)  They are also very accommodating to the vegetarian and gluten free crowd.

Amazing fish tacos, phenomenal beef tacos, okay veggie and chicken tacos.  The spicy jalapeno / cayenne cocktail is out of the world good.  Giving this place 4 stars just because I expected the chicken tacos to be more high caliber.
it so nasty foods it get me sick
The most excellent service, food, & their own created alcohols! Def recommend checking out the location on Sangamon St and Lake St at the MORGAN CTA STATION of the GREEN & Pink Line!

Come for the tacos, stay because you ordered the margarita double.  Food is good, drinks are very good.  Price is reasonable for the area.  Tip: the bathrooms have a squirrel head or a squirrel tail on the doors.  I've stood there trying to decide which one was for me.  They're unisex so choose either one.
to expensive !
Fantastic tacos. Seriously tried 8 different kinds and all of them were awesome. Decent wait staff. Its got a Diner feel with tight quarters though.

Absolutely love this modern rustic Mexican fusion restaurant.  Interior are cozy with mason jar candles everywhere and unique decor on wall.  Great for a date night or with friends.  Food was delicious and unique.  Salsas were pistachio green, habanero hibiscus and red salsa.  All were really good fresh with little kick.  Tacos were made very fresh and from scratch which took a bit time despite few people were in the restaurant at the late hour in middle of week.  They offer vegan and vegetarian option.  Drinks were delicious especially Michaelada was the best ever with a good blend of salt and spicy kick.  Staff were friendly, kind and good service.

Checked this place out couple days back and I can't wait to go back.  Their tacos are off the chain good even if a little on the pricy side.  The deliciousness doesn't stop there, try out their three salsas and the fineeee drinks.  I got the michelada and wowsers it was good and spicy made just perfect.  This is also def a good place for a date night because of their awesome interior and low light ambience.

Yummy unique tacos and salsas! The mole chicken is tender and well sliced. We also had the cheese tacos and vegan tacos. The cheese ones have a fancy name and its a thick slice of a hearty grilled cheese. The salsas ranged from ghost pepper to rhubarb to pistachio. Cocktails were all solid and complex in favor.

Like I read, do not let the awning fool you. Great lighting, good music and killer tacos. Yum yum yum. Cocktails y agua fresca are delish. We were able to try both postres but only liked the one we didn't order....4 stars be they give small rations of the salsa and pickled veggies which was not enough.  So worth the visit.

This is for delivery. My husband and I were feeling lazy, and we decided to give a new place a try, and we are so glad we did. Delivery was on the quicker side. It took just about 30 minutes for our order to show up from the time that we placed it.  Our order: large fish tacos, roasted winter squash, smoked tomato rice, and the hearts of palm salad.  We truly enjoyed everything we ordered. The stand-out in the group was the roasted winter squash! Very flavorful with spice and a little kick. Also noteworthy was the sauce on the fish tacos - really added something different to the usual mix of fish tacos in the city. I would like to try them in-restaurant as I imagine the breading would be crispier. That said, the breading is great - not too heavy and not dripping with grease.  We will definitely be ordering again and visiting in person to try more options on the menu!
I love takito! Such wonderful flavors.... The drink menu is so unique and fresh. I love the redfish tacos and creamy polenta. I could eat here multiple times a week.

A fantastic new restaurant, finding it's niche in the locally-sourced, modern Mexican/Latin cuisine. It's disappointing that they're not open for lunch during the week. I would go there every day.  The have a creative selection of sharable dishes with an emphasis on seasonal, including an new set of Chef's Specials every week. Also, try the homemade salsas & margaritas as well, I had the week's special of guanciale tacos, which were, crisp, fatty &, to say the least, finger-lickin great.

This is another hip and modern taco place with prices slightly above what you'd want to pay for tacos. Luckily, the food is delicious, making it worth a visit. I highly recommend both the crab tacos and the fish tacos with the classic salsa to start. The classic margarita was one of the best I've had with the right mix of sweet and salt (salt is added in a cool patch on the side, not just the rim). I'd eat at Takito again.

HOLY GRAIL!  #JAYZjustintimberlake  This place was twerking for me!  #ilovemiley,not!  We got to sit outside on a beautiful night.  #chicagoweatherhasbeencrazy  The food was so amazing.  #imafatpig polenta was creamy, cheesy, bacon-NESS. whats not to love. could've ate the whole dish myself. heart of palms salad was so refreshing and crisp tacos.  we had the crispy redfish and the lamb chirizo.  both amazing.  would highly recommend them. chocolate ganache. yummy, however i didnt like the aesthetic of the dish it was in. if you didnt dig down with your spoon, you didnt get the chocolate. rice pudding was creamy and sweet!  MMMMmmm  They have lots of different kinds of drinks.  Margarita flavors galore.  Long list of whatever you could possibly want!  Only thing that I found annoying was that you cant mix and match tacos.  All 3 the same.  Oh, and it was reasonable in price.  Valet was $10.  It was damn good.  I would definitely be back
The tacos are very tasty. The tacos are very small, recommend getting appetizer or two orders of tacos.

Let's just get this out of the way: the tacos are expensive. Not lobster dinner expensive, but not the cheap eats tacos are meant to be. Three - five dollars per taco is stretching the limits of credulity. Still, the tacos are good.  We ordered the Alaskan King Crab tacos and their special, which involved pork shoulder and chapulines (crickets). The crab tacos were excellent: buttery and rich with a kick of spice. The pork shoulder tacos were great too, though the chewiness of the chapulines was a bit unnerving compared with the soft give of the thinly shredded pork shoulder. We also ordered the tomatillo pistachio salsa, which was delicious and surprisingly complex thanks to the nuttiness from the pistachios. So the food is great, albeit a bit overpriced.  The ambiance was classic Wicker Park, and the lighting is really attractive. The chairs, it must be mentioned, are not very comfortable--too high and too metal. That said: if you want fancied up tacos, head here.

From the name, I thought this was a Japanese restaurant, but upon the visit, learned that it was a Latin-inspired place. The interior is quite nice, with the industrial look and feel. The staff was wonderful and the food and drink selection was marvelous. It was a great time on west division that night.

very casual place with really substantial food.  the drinks are made to order and they aren't something that you would normally see. the pork belly is delicious- super savory and melt in your mouth type.  it was easy to make reservations, but kind of hard to find parking at.

Had an amazing brunch experience. Very attentive staff, well prepared and thought over food. You will not be dissapointed. Everyone was extremely friendly as well. Would definitely come here again, and recommend to friends.

We stopped in here to try out a new place. We were definitely impressed by the flavorful tacos. However, they were pricey and very small. I would suggest trying it out once, but don't expect to walk out full up!

Deceiving small appearance from the outside, but surprisingly spacious inside.  A cool, industrial decor and nice features like motion-sensor lights in the bathrooms.  Definitely eat here if you have a sophisticated palate and enjoy eating with your eyes--beautiful presentations and creative ingredients abound.  The knowledgable servers will be happy to tell you which farm sourced the strawberries for the amazing, seasonal margarita flavor, and know the menu as well as they should to be able to make stellar recommendations.

Very nice place, service is really good, especially Josh, our very friendly waiter. Food was excellent, portions were a good size, not too big, not too small. Tomatillo rice was very tasty. Strong in alcohol margarita. Recommended place.
